Class AccountCredentials

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.kennedyoliveira.pastebin4j.AccountCredentials

  • public class AccountCredentials
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the account credentials for logging into the API and fetch informations.
    Since:
    1.0.0

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      AccountCredentials(java.lang.String devKey)
      This constructor without the userName and password is limited about the interaction with the API.
      AccountCredentials(java.lang.String devKey, java.lang.String userName, java.lang.String password)
      Setup the credentials for logging into the API using the username and password provided, this enables to use all the features provided be the PasteBin API.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AccountCredentials

        public AccountCredentials(@NotNull
                          java.lang.String devKey)

        This constructor without the userName and password is limited about the interaction with the API.

        Using it you can only list trends pastes and create guest pastes, the other actions needs the userName and password.

        Parameters:
        devKey - API dev key, check the API documentation to see how to obtain one. http://pastebin.com/api#1

      • AccountCredentials

        public AccountCredentials(@NotNull
                          java.lang.String devKey,
                          @Nullable
                          java.lang.String userName,
                          @Nullable
                          java.lang.String password)

        Setup the credentials for logging into the API using the username and password provided, this enables to use all the features provided be the PasteBin API.

        Parameters:
        devKey - API dev key, check the API documentation to see how to obtain one. http://pastebin.com/api#1
        userName - Username to log into the API.
        password - Password to log into the API.

        public void setUserKey(java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> userKey)
